  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is typically defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions generally include:\n\n1. Key elements:\n- Concealing the origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal funds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Disguising the source of money obtained through criminal activity\n\n2. Common statutory definitions include:\n- Financial transactions intended to hide the source of illegal funds\n- Transferring money obtained from criminal activities\n- Attempting to make unlawful money appear legal\n\n3. Typical criminal activities generating laundered funds:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Illegal gambling\n- Organized crime\n\n4. Legal frameworks vary by jurisdiction, but most definitions involve:\n- Intent to conceal criminal proceeds\n- Deliberately obscuring money's illegal origin\n- Engaging in financial transactions to legitimize criminal funds\n\n5. International standards established by organizations like FATF provide consistent guidelines\n\nSpecific legal details can vary between countries and specific statutes. For precise definitions, consulting local legal codes or an attorney is recommended.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
